Reports gathered by National Daily have it that Burna Boy has revealed his plans to raise a child with his girlfriend, rapper Stefflon Don, away from public attention.
National Daily learnt that the Anybody singer expressed the desire to emulate his parents, Samuel and Bose Ogulu, in bringing up his child. He disclosed this on a radio show, Beats1, on Hot 97 FM in the U.S. recently.
Meanwhile, the Killing Demcrooner also wasted no time in publicly declaring his love for his British girlfriend Stefflon Don when he stressed that their affair was not a publicity stunt and that it meant so much to them.
According to him, “It is not the business part of us, it is our life. “I am trying to make it right because I don’t want to bring a kid into this life for anyone to be disturbing, looking or wondering what’s Stefflon Don and Burna Boy’s kid doing. “I want to raise a kid the way I was raised”
He further went to point out that his relationship with Stefflon was deep and that he would not want to publicize the details. For him, “It is lovely (being with Stefflon Don). I don’t know how to explain it. It’s just that I try to now kind of like keep it between us. “I don’t want to be putting our thing outthere in front of everybody anymore. Like you’d be there and you can see it, but I don’t want to put it out there for everyone”
 Recall that the Yawa Deysinger had in an interview with Ebro earlier in March, revealed that Stefflon was not just his girlfriend but ‘wifey’. A few months after, his British singer girlfriend had also revealed how she met him in Ghana and how she hopes they have kids together.
Report from NAN has it that Burna Boy is currently on a global media tour, following the release of his acclaimed album, African Giant.









			
